How can I change the icon of the accordion to a custom icon?

# Creating a Custom Accordion Icon in shadcn/ui

To customize the accordion icon in shadcn/ui, you'll need to modify the Accordion component itself rather than just the CSS. The default accordion uses a ChevronDown icon from the Lucide React library.

## Option 1: Modify the AccordionTrigger component

1. First, copy the Accordion component to your local components folder:
   ```bash
   npx shadcn-ui@latest add accordion
   ```

2. Then modify the `accordion.tsx` file in your components folder. Look for the `AccordionTrigger` component and replace the ChevronDown icon with your custom icon:

```jsx
import { YourCustomIcon } from "your-icon-library";

const AccordionTrigger = React.forwardRef<
  React.ElementRef<typeof AccordionPrimitive.Trigger>,
  React.ComponentPropsWithoutRef<typeof AccordionPrimitive.Trigger>
>(({ className, children, ...props }, ref) => (
  <AccordionPrimitive.Header className="flex">
    <AccordionPrimitive.Trigger
      ref={ref}
      className={cn(
        "flex flex-1 items-center justify-between py-4 font-medium transition-all hover:underline [&[data-state=open]>svg]:rotate-180",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
      <YourCustomIcon className="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" />
    </AccordionPrimitive.Trigger>
  </AccordionPrimitive.Header>
))
```

## Option 2: Use CSS to hide the default icon and add your own

If you don't want to modify the component itself, you can use CSS to hide the default icon and add your own:

```css
/* In your CSS file or component */
.custom-accordion-trigger svg {
  display: none;
}

.custom-accordion-trigger::after {
  content: "";
  background-image: url('/path-to-your-icon.svg');
  background-size: contain;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  width: 16px;
  height: 16px;
  display: inline-block;
  transition: transform 0.2s;
}

.custom-accordion-trigger[data-state="open"]::after {
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}

/* Apply the class to your Accordion component */
<Accordion type="single" collapsible>
  <AccordionItem value="item-1">
    <AccordionTrigger className="custom-accordion-trigger">
      Is it accessible?
    </AccordionTrigger>
    <AccordionContent>
      Yes. It adheres to the WAI-ARIA design pattern.
    </AccordionContent>
  </AccordionItem>
</Accordion>
```

Option 1 is generally preferred as it's cleaner and more maintainable, allowing you to fully customize the icon component with proper accessibility attributes.
